Package seng202.group5.logic

Class Till

  • java.lang.Object
    • seng202.group5.logic.Till
  • public class Till
extends java.lang.Object
    Till class keeps track of held denominations value and how many are held. Has methods to calculate the total amount held and methods to calculate change.

      • addDenomination

        public void addDenomination​(org.joda.money.Money value,
                            int count)
        Adds the given value to the denominations stored. If a given denomination does not exist, it is added to the denominations HashMap.
        Parameters:
        value - holds the value of a denomination using Joda Money.
        count - The number of denominations to be added.

      • removeDenomination

        public void removeDenomination​(org.joda.money.Money value,
                               int count)
                        throws InsufficientCashException
        Removes a number stated by count worth of denominations from the held denominations. Assumes only valid money values will be selected from other methods.
        Parameters:
        value - holds the value of a denomination using Joda Money.
        count - The number of denominations to be added.
        Throws:
        InsufficientCashException - when there are not enough denominations to remove.

      • addDenominations

        public void addDenominations​(java.util.HashMap<org.joda.money.Money,​java.lang.Integer> valueMap)
        Adds multiple denominations by calling addDenomination multiple times. Further assumes that only valid money values wil be selected from other methods.
        Parameters:
        valueMap - Uses the Money type as a key and the number of denominations to be removed.

      • totalValue

        public org.joda.money.Money totalValue()
        Returns the total amount of money held as a sum. Calls Joda-Moneys method multipliedBy().
        Returns:
        totalSum, the total of all denominations multiplied by the number counted.
